    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@teramind I personally think the mailing list is better for such more general questions (unless you think it is a bug or a clear enhancement proposal), but it is also not a problem to bring it up here.\n\nAs you can read in the docs (http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/dsintro.html#series), `Series` is the 1d structure in pandas, so it is logical to get that when requesting a column I think. As it is 1d, it has also some other functionality compared to a 1-column dataframe that make less sense for a DataFrame (eg value_counts).\n"
